---
const GITHUB = 'https://github.com/lima3w/padduck';
const WIKI   = 'https://github.com/lima3w/padduck/wiki';

const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'Is Padduck production ready?',
    a: 'Padduck is in public beta. The core IPAM features — subnet management, IP allocation, discovery, and the REST API — are stable and used in real deployments. The API is versioned and will not introduce breaking changes within a major version. We recommend reading the changelog before upgrading.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What does IPAM stand for?',
    a: 'IP Address Management. IPAM tools help you track, allocate, and document IP addresses, subnets, VLANs, and related network resources. Padduck focuses on making this structured and automatable without the complexity of a full network source-of-truth platform.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Does it require Kubernetes or complex infrastructure?',
    a: 'No. Padduck is designed to be self-hosted with Docker Compose. You need Docker, a machine to run it on, and about two minutes. There is no Kubernetes, no service mesh, no cloud dependency.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Can it run on low-end hardware?',
    a: 'Yes. The Go backend is lightweight. A small VPS or homelab machine with 1–2 GB of RAM and a modest CPU is sufficient for most deployments. The main resource consumer is PostgreSQL, which you can tune to your environment.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What authentication methods are supported?',
    a: 'Padduck supports local accounts with TOTP two-factor authentication, LDAP directory integration, OAuth2 (e.g. GitHub, Google, Authentik), and SAML2 for enterprise SSO. You can mix local and external auth.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Is the REST API stable?',
    a: 'Yes. The REST API is OpenAPI-documented and versioned. API v1 is frozen — no breaking changes within the v1 series. The API is the primary integration surface; automation is a first-class use case, not an afterthought.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Is Padduck open source? What is the license?',
    a: 'Yes. Padduck is released under the GNU General Public License v3.0 (GPL-3.0). The full source code is available on GitHub. You are free to use, modify, and self-host it.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Can I contribute?',
    a: 'Absolutely. The repository is open on GitHub. Check the issue tracker for open bugs and feature requests, or open a discussion to propose something new. Pull requests are welcome.',
  },
];
---
<section class="section faq-section" id="faq">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="faq-header">
      <p class="eyebrow">FAQ</p>
      <h2 class="faq-title">Common questions.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-grid">
      {faqs.map((item, i) => (
        <details class="faq-item" name="faq">
          <summary class="faq-q">
            <span>{item.q}</span>
            <svg class="faq-icon" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true">
              <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="faq-a">{item.a}</p>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="faq-footer">
      <p>More questions?</p>
      <a href={`${GITHUB}/issues`} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-outline">Open an issue on GitHub</a>
      <a href={WIKI} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-ghost">Browse the docs →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
.faq-section {
  background: linear-gradient(180deg, #020812 0%, rgba(7, 22, 43, 0.4) 50%, #020812 100%);
}

.faq-header {
  text-align: center;
  margin-bottom: 56px;
}
.faq-title {
  font-size: clamp(1.9rem, 4vw, 3rem);
  margin-top: 16px;
}

.faq-grid {
  max-width: 820px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 8px;
}

.faq-item {
  background: linear-gradient(160deg, rgba(10, 31, 58, 0.6), rgba(7, 22, 43, 0.4));
  border: 1px solid var(--line-md);
  border-radius: var(--r-lg);
  overflow: hidden;
  transition: border-color 0.2s;
}
.faq-item[open] {
  border-color: rgba(245, 184, 0, 0.22);
}

.faq-q {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 16px;
  padding: 20px 24px;
  cursor: pointer;
  list-style: none;
  font-weight: 700;
  font-size: 0.98rem;
  color: var(--white);
  transition: color 0.15s;
}
.faq-q::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
.faq-q:hover { color: var(--gold-2); }
.faq-q span { flex: 1; }

.faq-icon {
  flex-shrink: 0;
  color: var(--muted-2);
  transition: transform 0.25s ease;
}
.faq-item[open] .faq-icon { transform: rotate(180deg); }

.faq-a {
  padding: 0 24px 24px;
  color: var(--muted);
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  line-height: 1.75;
}

.faq-footer {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  gap: 16px;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  margin-top: 56px;
}
.faq-footer p {
  color: var(--muted-2);
  font-size: 0.95rem;
}
</style>
